{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GjeNVM2rrTSpVgc8rG8Bb2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear from the describe output. The `crdb-cluster-1` pod has its HTTP address bound to `127.0.0.1:8080` (localhost only) instead of `0.0.0.0:8080`. This is intentional based on the startup command:\n\n```\nif [ \"$POD_NAME\" = \"crdb-cluster-1\" ]; then\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"127.0.0.1:8080\";\nelse\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"0.0.0.0:8080\";\nfi\n```\n\nSo the health probe `http://10.244.0.234:8080/health?ready=1` is failing because the HTTP server is only listening on `127.0.0.1:8080` (not externally accessible), but the readiness probe is hitting the pod's IP `10.244.0.234:8080`.\nThe fix is to modify the StatefulSet's startup command so that `crdb-cluster-1` binds to all interfaces instead of just localhost. I need to examine the StatefulSet spec and update the conditional logic that's restricting the HTTP address.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5553,"cache_read_input_tokens":30112,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5553},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"88722c13-9118-462c-9429-fe610f95e6ca","uuid":"0a04c46c-4a88-4a3f-99e9-0e8dcb1a7e00","request_id":"req_011Cc48oAAjL5RuT7sV7sDbm"}
