{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0135rAikVtWL14FBa9xrkCE4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The bug is in the StatefulSet command. For `crdb-cluster-1`, it hardcodes `HTTP_ADDR=\"127.0.0.1:8080\"` (localhost only), but for other pods it uses `0.0.0.0:8080`. This means the HTTP server for `crdb-cluster-1` is not accessible from outside the pod, so the readiness probe (which tries to hit the pod IP `10.244.0.234:8080`) fails.\n\nThe fix is to patch the StatefulSet to remove the `crdb-cluster-1` special case and always use `0.0.0.0:8080` for all pods. \n\nPatching the StatefulSet will trigger a rolling restart of `crdb-cluster-1` with the corrected binding.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2533,"cache_read_input_tokens":35665,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2533},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"88722c13-9118-462c-9429-fe610f95e6ca","uuid":"7c99b5a7-b252-4340-8736-a65ce50bfa74","request_id":"req_011Cc48ovPXxiYss1ThmeKWB"}
