{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015cmBRXLGz4GdBe6262ZxgP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cluster is fully healthy:\n\n- **All 3 pods**: `1/1 Running` with 0 restarts\n- **All 3 nodes**: `is_live=true`, `is_available=true`\n- **SQL**: responding normally\n\n**Root cause**: The StatefulSet startup command had been patched with a conditional that forced `crdb-cluster-1` to bind its HTTP server to `127.0.0.1:8080` (localhost only) instead of `0.0.0.0:8080`. The Kubernetes readiness probe hits the pod's cluster IP (`10.244.0.234:8080`), which is unreachable when the server only listens on loopback — so the probe failed, the pod was removed from the Service, and the cluster degraded.\n\n**Fix**: Patched the StatefulSet to remove the per-pod conditional and use `--http-addr=0.0.0.0:8080` for all pods. The rolling update then recreated both `crdb-cluster-1` and `crdb-cluster-2` with the correct binding."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":562,"cache_read_input_tokens":50169,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":562},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"88722c13-9118-462c-9429-fe610f95e6ca","uuid":"098ef465-47cd-495a-8e3e-ab5b19d3887b","request_id":"req_011Cc49AZUGrtfgysPKgqmjV"}
